            "body": "Thanks for mentioning this. This was a hidden bug that is now exposed since the servername is now validated. Before https://github.com/neovim/neovim/commit/96128a5076b7e45fc01163151401a9e2acdff565 , `NVIM_APPNAME=test_configs/test nvim` would silently fail to create a server and `v:servername` would be empty.\r\n\r\nWithout `--listen`, Nvim generates a servername based on `$XDG_STATE_HOME` (which is influenced by `NVIM_APPNAME`). It seems that `server_start` is failing for the `NVIM_APPNAME=test_configs/test` case.",
